SIMPLE: why
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Why
<hw>Why</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>whi</ets>,
<ets>why</ets>, AS. <ets>hw⟦imac⟧</ets>, <ets>hw<?/</ets>, instrumental
case of <ets>hw⟦amac⟧</ets>, <ets>hw⟦ae⟧t</ets>; akin to Icel.
<ets>hv⟦imac⟧</ets> why, Dan. & Sw. <ets>hvi</ets>; cf. Goth.
<ets>hw<?/</ets>. <?/. See <er>Who</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>For what cause, reason, or purpose; on what account;
wherefore; -- used interrogatively. See the Note under <er>What</er>,
<xex>pron</xex>., 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Turn ye, turn ye from your evil ways; for <qex>why</qex> will ye
die, O house of Israel?</q> <rj><qau>Ezek. xxxiii. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>For which; on account of which; -- used
relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No ground of enmity between us known⟦br⟧
<qex>Why</qex> he should mean me ill or seek to harm.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Turn the discourse; I have a reason <qex>why</qex>⟦br⟧
I would not have you speak so tenderly.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The reason or cause for which; that on account of
which; on what account; <as>as, I know not <ex>why</ex> he left town so
suddenly</as>; -- used as a compound relative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<note><p>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Why</xex> is sometimes used as an interjection or
an expletive in expression of surprise or content at a turn of affairs;
used also in calling. ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Why</xex>, Jessica!⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If her chill heart I can not move,⟦br⟧
<qex>Why</qex>, I'll enjoy the very love.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>Sometimes, also, it is used as a noun.⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The how and the <qex>why</qex> and the where.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></note>

<p><cs><col><b>For why</b></col>, <cd>because; why. See
<er>Forwhy</er>.</cd> <mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Why</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Why
<hw>Why</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A young heifer.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Grose.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whydah finch</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Whydah bird</ent>⟦br⟧
